Elvish scripts.
Most samples of the Elvish language done by Tolkien were written out with the Latin alphabet, but within the fiction Tolkien imagined many writing systems for his Elves. The best-known are the "tengwar of F√´anor", but the first system he created, c. 1919, is the "tengwar of R√∫mil", also called the sarati.
