Internal history of the scripts.
Prior to their exile, the Elves of the Second Clan (the Noldor) used first the sarati of R√∫mil to record their tongue, Quenya. In Middle-earth, Sindarin was first recorded using the "Elvish runes" or cirth, named later "certar" in Quenya. A runic inscription in Quenya was engraved on the sword of Aragorn (II), And√∫ril.

